lead_paragraph: Rangers forward Brandon Dubinsky scored three goals and the United States (3-2) scored three times in each period to wrap up its qualifying round at the world championship with a 9-1 victory over Norway in Halifax, Nova Scotia. The Americans will play Finland in the quarterfinals.
